
Converter of Extended Finite Automata [1] from Supremica Waters modules [2] to NuSMV [3], as described in [4] and [5].


Building
--------
Maven [6] is used to build the converter:

  mvn clean package


Running
-------

1. As a GUI

  Double-click on the jar-with-dependencies file in the target folder;

  or

  java -jar target/efa2nusmv-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar


2. As a command-line tool

  java -jar target/efa2nusmv-1.0-SNAPSHOT-jar-with-dependencies.jar input-file-name [output-file-name]




References
----------

[1]. Supervisory Control Applied to Automata Extended with Variables - Revised, Markus Sköldstam, Knut Åkesson, and Martin Fabian. Technical Report R001/2008, Department of Signals and Systems, Chalmers University of Technology, Göteborg, Sweden, 2008.

[2]. http://www.supremica.org

[3]. http://nusmv.fbk.eu/ or http://nusmv.irst.itc.it/

[4]. Alexey Voronov and Knut Åkesson. Verification of Supervisory Control Properties of Finite Automata Extended with Variables. Technical Report R-003/2009, Chalmers University of Technology. Available online: http://publications.lib.chalmers.se/records/fulltext/94442.pdf

[5]. Alexey Voronov and Knut Åkesson. Verification of Process Operations Using Model Checking. Automation Science and Engineering, 2009. CASE 2009. IEEE International Conference on , p. 415-420. DOI 10.1109/COASE.2009.5234103

[6]. apache.maven.org






